The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                          Thursday , November 19 , 2009                                                                                                                                                                                            IN THE CITY
                    
	Calcutta: The Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) has asked Bengal team manager Russi Jeejeebhoy to submit a specific report on the captaincy controversy. The CAB has also set a 24-hour deadline, after the completion of Bengals Ranji Trophy Super League match against Karnataka, under way at Mysore, for the same.      
	Jeejeebhoy has been asked to explain the reasons behind naming Manoj Tiwary the captain when president Jagmohan Dalmiya and other CAB officials wanted Deep Dasgupta to lead the side in Laxmi Ratan Shuklas absence.      
	Meanwhile, Rohan Gavaskar will undergo a fitness test on Sunday before Bengals next Ranji match against Saurashtra, at the Eden, from November 24.       
	The Bengal team will also be selected on the same day. According to sources, Rohan, Sourav Ganguly and Shukla are set to return to the team.                                                                                                                                                                       
